HEADWORD: Prutenic
<hw>Pru*ten"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>
<def>Prussian; -- applied to certain astronomical tables published in
the sixteenth century, founded on the principles of Copernicus, a
Prussian.</def>⟦br⟧
